The paper discusses the implementation of cryptographic protocols, specifically key-exchange protocols, for oblivious transfer. This topic falls under the category of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper involves information theory (cs.IT) as it deals with the exchange of secrets and encryption keys. The paper also involves computational complexity (cs.CC) as it presents protocols for 1-out-of-2 OT and coin-flipping. The paper may also fall under the category of Computer Engineering (cs.CE) as it discusses the implementation of cryptographic schemes. Finally, the paper may fall under the category of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) as it presents protocols for exchanging keys and secrets.
